This paper proposes a novel inductive matrix completion model based on graph neural networks. The model does not use any side information and achieves highly competitive performance with state-of-the-art transductive baselines. The paper falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it proposes a new model for matrix completion. It also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it uses graph neural networks. The paper also falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI) as it deals with rating matrices and subgraphs. Information retrieval (cs.IR) is another possible category as the paper involves predicting ratings. Finally, data structures (cs.DS) is a possible category as the paper involves manipulating matrices and subgraphs.
